    Page: 43
Title: Biding One's Time
---
The responses of human beings vary greatly under dangerous circumstances. The
strong man advances boldly to meet them head on. The weak man grows
agitated. But the superior man stands up to fate, endures resolutely in
his inner certainty offinal success, and hides his time until the onset of
reassuring odds.
